              \frac{c_n}{c_{n+1}} \right| 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              R \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \left|
              \frac{\frac{1}{\sqrt{n+1}}}{\frac{1}{\sqrt{n+2}}} 
              \right| 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} 
              \frac{\sqrt{n+2}}{\sqrt{n+1}} = 1 
            </mrow>
          </md>
          The numerator and denominator have the same asymptotic order
          and the leading coefficients are both 1, so the limit is 1.
          The radius of convergence is 1. 
        </p>
      </solution>
