              \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \left|
              \frac{\frac{n!}{(2n!}}{\frac{(n+1)!}{(2n+2)!}} 
              \right| 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} 
              \frac{n! (2n+2)!}{(n+1)! (2n)!}
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} 
              \frac{(2n+2)(2n+1)}{n+1)} = \infty 
            </mrow>
          </md>
          The numerator has higher asymptotic order, so the limit is
          <m>\infty</m>. The radius of convergence is <m>\infty</m>. 
        </p>
      </solution>
