              \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \left|
              \frac{\frac{1}{n+\cos (\pi
              n)}}{\frac{1}{n+1+\cos(\pi(n+1))}} \right| 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \amp = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} 
              \frac{n + 1 + \cos(\pi(n+1))}{n + \cos (\pi n)} = 1
            </mrow>
          </md>
          Both denominator and numerator have the same asymptotic
          order and the leading coefficients are both 1, so the limit
          is 1. (Note that the cosine term, since it doesn't grow at
          all, has no effect on the asymptotic order.) The radius of
          convergence is 1.
        </p>
